Description: Stem and tondo sherd of Attic, probably black-figured, pottery cup, probably of type A; interior: part of tondo surrounded by at least two lines: part of a male figure to right (part of elbow with added red on upper arm and possible trace of foot); exterior: glazed black.
Curator's comments: There are deposits on the exterior surface of the sherd.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0627) (Phase 1)
